reviewText: I highly recommend this DVD.  The production quality isn't great, so there are times when the music is too loud and the instructor is a bit drowned out by it.  However, you can always hear her well enough to follow.  The workout itself is worth the annoyance of the music.There are several sections to the workout, so you can skip forward or back to different parts and change your routine whenever you want.  The instructor keeps you looking at your heart rate monitor (if you are wearing one... it's not required) so you can see how your body is responding.  I was surprised to find that, even during sections where the workout seemed easier, my heart rate always stays right in my target zone.  I burn lots of calories while enjoying the work.  I never get bored.  I never feel overexerted.Amazon doesn't offer the DVD right now, but you can order it directly from the "Hollywood Trainer" web site.  My DVD got to me lightening fast.  Great service!If you are looking for more fun kickboxing aerobic DVDs, try these:Janis Saffell Kickbox Strike Zone(Easy- Intermediate Level Workout)Hardcore Kickbox Circuit(Intermediate- Advanced Level Workout)
summary: Terrific Workout! Fun and Even Paced to Keep Your Heart Rate Up w/out Feeling Exhausted.

reviewText: This is one fabulous kickboxing dvd - always my go to when I only have 45 minutes or so to spare and need to feel revitatlised.  Jeannette Jenkins is a terrific instructor - she explains and cues well, and is cheerful without being annoyingly upbeat.  There are no time for breaks here, but the two strength intervals let you catch your breath even though your limbs might be initially screaming... all in a good way -this is a truly effective workout and you won't believe how good you feel after you've done it.  I've previously done the 10 minute solutions kickbox dvds (with Jessica Smith and Keli Roberts) : this one is much more intense.Agree that the music is could be much better, as could the production values and set, but once you get kicking, punching and doing all those repeater knees under Jeannette's excellent instruction, it won't really  matter.

reviewText: I was first introduced to Ms. Jenkins on the exercise channel.  She seemed very knowledgeable and 'perky.'  I loved this sweat inducing workout so much that I had to purchase it.  I wouldn't label it hardcore but you will work and burn calories.  She will also get you HIGH...naturally of course, so if you are a seeker of the mysterious endorphin high this is the workout for you.  She's in my top ten of kick butt trainers.
